How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

J. Marvel
2.0 out of 5 stars Enjoyed it for a while, then had a bad reaction
Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2023
Scent: Lavender & SageVerified Purchase
I have used Dove deodorant for years but wanted to try an aluminum free option. I looked into the best kind for women going through hormonal changes as I have recently entered surgical menopause and it's a pretty drastic change for my body chemically. After a bit of research I landed on Salt & Stone as being the best option for me.

I still had some remaining Dove leftover so I initially used the Salt & Stone interchangeably with the Dove in order to not waste. After the Dove was depleted I switched to only using Salt & Stone. I found the Salt & Stone to be a little dry in the application but other than that it had a pleasant scent but not too overpowering and it actually worked well. I don't typically have a problem with body odor but as mentioned my body is going through some interesting changes chemically so I didn't want to risk it.

After about 1 month of continuous use I noticed my armpits started to be itchy. I attributed this to the rather dryness of the application and didn't think much more. When the itchiness persisted I also started noting that it felt as if I had welts or hives on my armpits. After another week or so I decided to look in the mirror and noticed redness and dry/flaky skin in and around my armpit area.

I have since switched back to my old trusty Dove deodorant and the issues cleared up immediately. I am not someone with allergies or sensitivities so this was a unique experience for me and I can't narrow down the culprit in the Salt & Stone easily due to this.

I really wish this would have worked for me long term because it was a good experience until the reaction started.
